# B.A.M.B.I. Web Admin Panel — Environment Variables
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in real values.
# The .env file must sit in the project root (parent of src/).
# It is loaded by src/hmac_client.py at startup.
#
# NEVER commit the real .env to git.

# ── HMAC Authentication ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# The proxy signs every request to the AutomatApp API with HMAC-SHA256.
# These credentials must match an HMACToken row in the AutomatApp database.
#
# How to get them:
#   1. Open the AutomatApp desktop application.
#   2. Navigate to the HMAC key management screen (from the main view).
#   3. Enter a name for the new key (e.g. "webpanel") and click OK.
#   4. The app shows "name:secret" — copy both parts below.
#   5. Optionally the secret is also transmitted via netcat if you enter
#      an IP address in the dialog that appears (run: nc -l 12345 on receiver).
#
HMAC_KEY_ID=your_key_name_here
HMAC_SECRET=your_very_long_base64_secret_here
